The course is closely associated with a specific international law moot court, e.g. Jessup or Telders. During the first phase, the students prepare the written memorials of both parties.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To gain a deeper theoretical understanding of international law and to get practical litigation experience while participating in the international law moot courtLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has passed the course: -- gains more detailed knowledge in specific issues and fields of international law -- solves complex cases concerning international law -- prepares appropriate written memorials -- commands legal English and pleading techniques -- gets practical litigation experience
